  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SDC Primary Health Care Project Inception</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will enable the conflicted population in Kawkareik to be able to access to quality health care.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project targets people in conflict affected areas in Kawkareik township but are under the governmane controlled areas in Karen State. CA will be in consortium with Save the Children and Karen Baptist Convention to work in these areas. There will be components of health system strengthening which will be led by Save the Children using their Comprehensive Township Health Planning tools. This will help identify health needs and system weaknesses in the township and will be able to build the capacity of the Township Health Departments. CA will support KBC to work on demand side for quality health services and to facilitate the creation of linkages between township health departments and village level health committees and health workers. Referral path ways will be built up and emergency health funds will support communities to be able to access quality health care. CA will support KBC in developing accountability framework and community empowerment through the use of PVCA tools. The consortium is called PHASE-M and will work closely with the other consortium led by CPI which will facilitate among the ethnic health organizations which will cover the ethnic armed group controlled areas. This will enable the full coverage of Kawkare</narrative>
  </description>
